HEADWORD: Erubescency
<hw>Er`u*bes"cen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>erubescentia</ets>: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧rubescence</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act of becoming red; redness of the skin or surface of
anything; a blushing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

